'''Mark Delany''' is an Australian computer programmer and consultant specializing in [[email|e-mail]] infrastructure and [[Antispam|anti-spam techniques]].
He is the chief architect and inventor of [[DomainKeys]],<ref>[http://yodel.yahoo.com/2007/05/22/one-small-step-for-email-one-giant-leap-for-internet-safety/ Yodel Anecdotal » Blog Archive » One small step for email, one giant leap for Internet safety<!-- Bot generated title -->]</ref><ref>{{US patent|6986049}}</ref> an [[e-mail authentication]] system designed to verify the [[DNS domain]] of an [[e-mail]] sender and the [[message integrity]]. Mark is one of the authors of [[DomainKeys Identified Mail]],<ref>[http://www.ietf.org/rfc/rfc4871.txt RFC 4871 - The DKIM Base Specification]</ref> a development of DomainKeys.
He was also lead architect for [[Yahoo mail|Yahoo! Mail]].<ref>[http://yhoo.client.shareholder.com/press/releasedetail.cfm?ReleaseID=245175 Yahoo! Inc. - Press Release<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080102013843/http://yhoo.client.shareholder.com/press/ReleaseDetail.cfm?ReleaseID=245175 |date=2008-01-02 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url =http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/technology/6688675.stm|title =Backing for tool to battle spam|publisher =[[BBC News]]|date =2007-05-24|accessdate = 2008-01-17 }}</ref>
