===Lift and Escalator Industry Association=== The Lift and Escalator Industry Association (LEIA) is an advisory body for the [[elevator|lift]] and [[escalator]] industry. It was formed in 1997 through the merger of two-long standing associations dating back to 1932.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://books.google.com/books?ei=u1jVT4O9J6nw0gGetvyvAw&id=_5vGAAAAIAAJ&dq=%22Lift+and+Escalator+Industry+Association%22&q=%22Lift+and+Escalator+Industry+Association%22#search_anchor |title=Lift associations opt to unite |volume=19 |work=Building Services Journal |page=9 |accessdate=11 June 2012}}</ref> They represent around 95% of specialist contractors in its sector.
The LEIA operates Liftex,<ref>'''LiftEx''' [http://www.beyondrigging.com/2014/03/liftex/ "''LiftEx 2014''"]</ref> a [[trade show]] and exhibition for the lifts and escalator industry, every three years.<ref>{{cite journal |last=O'Guynn |first=Brad |year=2010 |title=Events: Liftex 2010 Lift and Escalator Industry Association opens exhibition participation to non-members and draws increased visitors. |journal=Elevator World |volume=58 |issue=7 |page=99 |issn=0013-6158}}</ref> The next LEIA exhibition will be Liftex 2019 on 15-16 May 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.liftex2019.com/|title=Liftex 2013|accessdate=11 November 2017}}</ref> A different exhibition with a similar name is operated by the Lifting Equipment Engineers Association.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.liftex.org |title=LiftEx 2017 |publisher=Lifting Equipment Engineers Association |accessdate=11 November 2017}}</ref>
